# Fluff Date: 2026-02-19 16:29:24
overview:<p>The Snow Fox is Clan Ice Hellion's attempt to create a fast, multi-role light 'Mech built around a quad chassis. Introduced around 3015 during the Golden Century, the design was produced at Hector MechWorks Facility Beta on the Ice Hellion homeworld of Hector. Built around the lightest version of the Hellion Slopeback quad chassis, the Snow Fox was deliberately designed to unsettle opponents, with aesthetics modeled after a swift predator native to Hector's icy plains.</p><p>The quad configuration served partly as an experiment by Hellion scientists to gauge warrior interest in four-legged designs as a potential stepping stone toward a quad OmniMech, though enthusiasm proved limited. Warriors generally preferred the familiarity and versatility of bipedal 'Mechs, and the Snow Fox's unusual loping gait required significant training to master. Despite these challenges, the design carved out a niche as an effective cavalry platform and battle armor hunter, using its exceptional speed to make slashing attacks before withdrawing.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Snow Fox is an extremely fast and agile 'Mech, propelled by a standard 160-rated fusion engine to speeds of 130 kilometers per hour. When the MASC system engages, that speed increases to a remarkable 172 kilometers per hour, making the Snow Fox one of the fastest quad designs ever fielded. This velocity is the design's primary weapon, allowing it to close rapidly, deliver strikes, and disengage before an effective response can be organized. The Snow Fox's unusual movement and MASC-enhanced bursts of speed make it a difficult target, often confounding enemy tracking systems.</p><p>Armament is deliberately light, consisting of a single Series 2f extended-range medium laser and two Series 1-s extended-range small lasers. This loadout generates minimal heat, and the ten single heat sinks handle the burden with ease. Four tons of Compound Alpha ferro-fibrous armor provide reasonable protection for a twenty-ton design, though concentrated fire remains dangerous. The narrow, low-slung profile inherent to the quad configuration partially compensates for the light armor by presenting a smaller target to opponents.</p>

deployment:<p>Introduced in 3072 during the Jihad, this variant represents a significant overhaul produced by the Eagle Craft Group under Clan Jade Falcon auspices. The standard engine is replaced with an extralight model, boosting top speed to 151 kilometers per hour while freeing tonnage for additional systems. The MASC system is removed in favor of an ECM suite integrated into the communications system, and the weaponry is completely revised to include an extended-range medium laser, a Type-3a ATM 3 launcher with two tons of ammunition, and two Tau-II anti-personnel Gauss rifles with one ton of ammunition. An endo steel internal structure saves further weight, though armor protection is slightly reduced. The design was observed in Jade Falcon service operating alongside light OmniMechs on Kikuyu during engagements with Lyran Alliance forces.</p>

history:<p>The Snow Fox entered service during the Golden Century as part of Clan Ice Hellion's ongoing efforts to field designs emphasizing speed above all other considerations. Production remained steady at Hector MechWorks Facility Beta under Ice Hellion control from the Late Succession Wars through the Civil War era. The design saw regular use in the Hellion touman alongside other light and medium 'Mechs that formed the backbone of the Clan's rapid-assault doctrine.</p><p>During the Hellion's Fury campaign of 3050, Snow Foxes served in the swift cavalry actions that characterized Ice Hellion operations across the Kerensky Cluster. In one engagement on the world of Marshall, an Ice Hellion Binary composed primarily of Snow Foxes raced around Falcon lines in the Firth mountain range, harassing targets along the rear flank. The rapid activity created the impression of a much larger force, allowing Hellion warriors an avenue of escape and an opportunity to turn the battle against the Jade Falcon defenders.</p><p>The Snow Fox also proved effective as a deterrent to Elemental headhunter Stars, where its speed and laser armament allowed it to swiftly crush surprise attacks before they could fully develop. As a second-line 'Mech, it appeared primarily in garrison and cavalry-style units, with the warriors of the Hellion Zeta Galaxy fielding a significant concentration of the design.</p><p>Following the destruction of Clan Ice Hellion during Operation ICE STORM and the Wars of Reaving, Hector and its production facilities passed to Clan Goliath Scorpion during the absorption of the Hellion remnants. The Jade Falcons also acquired at least one Snow Fox through the Harvest Trials, operating a modified example alongside light OmniMechs in their Occupation Zone. Production continued under new ownership, though the design's age and specialized quad configuration increasingly limited demand.</p>

